g = + qkXk + qkYk + qkZk (10)
where Xk, Ykand Zk are the Cartesian coordinates of atom k. The sign in Eq. 10 is considered positive if the calculated dipole moment vector has a positive scalar product with the correct dipole moment vector and negative if


