where 8kx is a Kronecker delta that is 1 if atom k has the atomic number o f atom X and 0 otherwise. Equation 15 remains valid for the CM1P model. Both models, as defined by Eqs. 3, 7, 15 and 18, are valid for c o m p o u n d s containing C, H, N, O, F, Si, S, C1, Br and I.
Table 16 gives the C M 1 A and CM1P parameters used to generate the mappings of the AM1 or PM3 Mulliken charges to the class IV charges. The scale factors and offsets are listed by atom type and charge model. These parameters define the CM1 models using Eqs. 3, 7, 15 and 18. We emphasize that the scale factors and offsets can only be applied in the context of the AM1 and PM3 wave functions, because Eqs. 15 and 18 also employ the AM1 or PM3 Mulliken charges, q(k°~, as well as the covalent bond indices [26], Bkk, , derived from the semiempirical wave function.
